title: Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit Premium 1.08.1.1044 + Keygen
description:
Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit Premium 1.08.1.1044 + Keygen (LATEST)



Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit is a straight foreward piece of software that protects your systemn's vulnerable points from web-based attacks.



The installation procedure takes little time to finish and does not need special attention from the user. At startup, Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit creates an icon in the system tray area (on the right of your screen by the clock) and activates the protection status.



You can bring up the main application windows to view total shielded applications, blocked exploit attempts and quarantined files.



In the secondary tab you can view the list of Thirt-Party applications that can be guarded by Malwarebytes Anti-Exploid. It includes Firefox, Google Chrome, Internet Explorer and Opera, Java, Adobe Acrobat, Microsoft Office tools (Word, Powerpoint, Excel), VLC Media Player, Windows Movie Maker and so on.



All activity is recorded to a log windows, selected entries can be excluded from the list as well as cleared. It is possible to create exclusions whern it comes to guarded applications. There are no other notable features provided by the application.



Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit runs on a barely noticeable amount of CPU and RAM, so it is not concern to the computer's overall performance. Since it minimizes to the taskbar, it does not interfere in the users regular activity.



I'm have not come across any issues througout my evaluation, as the app did not hang, crash or pop-up error dialogs. All in all, Malwarebytes Anti-Exploit is a simple yet effective tool for safe guarding programs against e-threats. Since it does not comprise a complex configuration set, the tool is accessable for advanced users as well as rookies.
